in, body sores, and pain or burning during urination. If a serious infection, an opportunistic infection, or sepsis develops, baricitinib should be interrupted until the infection is controlled.', 'Synergism', 'Artesunate, Mefloquine, Lumefantrine, Artemether, Pyrimethamine, Tafenoquine, Atovaquone, Hydroxychloroquine, Halofantrine, Quinine, Proguanil, More', 'Cyclosporine, Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Tocilizumab, Secukinumab, Canakinumab, Anifrolumab, Ravulizumab, Diroximel fumarate, Mycophenolic acid, Methotrexate, Abatacept, More', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/38866/', '[1] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[2] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[3] "Product Information. Olumiant (baricitinib)." Lilly, Eli and Company, Indianapolis, IN.[4] "Product Information. Lonsurf (tipiracil-trifluridine)." Taiho Oncology, Inc., Princeton, NJ.', 1767369485);
